Hi all,

I wrote a little test app to demonstrate the 
org.eclipse.debug.core.DebugException[5010]: org.eclipse.jdi.TimeoutException 
in Eclipse 2.10 (released version):

public class TestDebugDeepStack {

    private static final int DEPTH = 1500;
    private static int i = 0;   

	public static void main(String[] args) {
        recursive();
	}

    private static void recursive() {
      i++;
      switch (i) {
          case DEPTH:
            System.out.println("depth: " + i);
          break;
          case DEPTH+500:
            System.out.println("depth: " + i);
            System.exit(0);
          break;
      }
      recursive();
    }
}

Program works fine if you do not set any breakpoints.
If I create a breakpoint in line with System.exit(0); the exception is thrown.

Christoph

